  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Inhibition of dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-4) or sodium-glucose co-transporter type 2 (SGLT2)
      has been proposed as a therapeutic target for type 2 diabetes. However, how DPP-4 inhibitors
      or SGLT2 inhibitors exert protective actions for diabetic complications in addition to their
      glucose-lowering effects remains unknown.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
